<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Sex Is Never Casual</title>

<style>
body {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  background: #000;
  color: #fff;
  text-align: center;
}

.section {
  padding: 60px 20px;
  max-width: 700px;
  margin: auto;
}

h1 { font-size: 28px; }
p { font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.6; }

button {
  padding: 15px 25px;
  font-size: 16px;
  border: none;
  margin-top: 20px;
  cursor: pointer;
  background: white;
  color: black;
}

input {
  padding: 12px;
  width: 80%;
  margin-top: 15px;
}

.locked {
  filter: blur(7px);
}

.overlay {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.96);
  display: none;
  flex-direction: column;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 20px;
}

</style>
</head>

<body>

<!-- HOOK -->
<div class="section">
  <h1>You said it meant nothing.<br>So why does it still affect you?</h1>
  <p>This is not a book. This is a mirror.</p>
  <button onclick="startReading()">Start Reading</button>
</div>

<!-- EMAIL CAPTURE -->
<div class="section" id="emailSection" style="display:none;">
  <h2>Before you continue</h2>
  <p>Enter your email to access the reading experience</p>
  <input type="email" id="email" placeholder="Enter your email">
  <br>
  <button onclick="saveEmail()">Continue</button>
</div>

<!-- CONTENT -->
<div class="section" id="content" style="display:none;">

  <h2>CHAPTER 1: THE ILLUSION</h2>

  <p>There is a story most people live inside without realizing it.</p>

  <p>“It’s just physical.”<br>
  “It doesn’t mean anything.”<br>
  “We’re just having fun.”</p>

  <p>And for a moment, it feels true.</p>

  <p>But if that were actually true…</p>

  <p>You wouldn’t still remember certain people.</p>

  <p>You wouldn’t feel something when their name appears.</p>

  <p>You wouldn’t compare new connections to old ones.</p>

  <p><strong>Something stayed.</strong></p>

  <p>Even when the person left.</p>

  <p>And this is where it gets uncomfortable…</p>

  <div id="lockedPart" class="locked">

  <p><strong>Because the real question is:</strong></p>

  <p>What exactly happened to you?</p>

  <p>Why do certain people stay in your mind?</p>

  <p>Why does “casual” feel anything but casual?</p>

  <p>The answer is not what you think…</p>

  </div>

  <button onclick="showPaywall()">Continue Reading</button>

</div>

<!-- PAYWALL -->
<div class="overlay" id="paywall">

  <h2>🔒 Unlock Full Chapter</h2>

  <p>You’ve reached the point most people avoid.</p>

  <p>Inside the full book you’ll discover:</p>

  <p>
  • Why you can’t detach<br>
  • What intimacy does to your mind<br>
  • Why your patterns repeat<br>
  • How to regain control
  </p>

  <button onclick="payNow()">Unlock Now</button>

</div>

<script>

function startReading() {
  document.getElementById("emailSection").style.display = "block";
  window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);
}

function saveEmail() {
  let email = document.getElementById("email").value;
  if(email === "") {
    alert("Enter email");
    return;
  }

  localStorage.setItem("userEmail", email);

  document.getElementById("emailSection").style.display = "none";
  document.getElementById("content").style.display = "block";

  window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);
}

function showPaywall() {
  document.getElementById("paywall").style.display = "flex";
}

function payNow() {
  alert("Connect Paystack or Stripe here");
}

</script>

</body>
</html>
